calculate_efficiency_for_all_subjects(start: int = 3, end: int = 23, excluding: Optional[List[str]] = None) → dict[Any, dict[int, Union[float, int, Any]]]¶

Calculates the efficiency of all subjects in the dataset.

Args:

start (int): The index of the first trial to be included in the calculation (inclusive). end (int): The index of the last trial to be included in the calculation (exclusive). excluding (list): A list of subject names to be excluded from the calculation.

Returns:

A dictionary mapping subject names to their efficiency scores.

calculate_efficiency_for_one_subject(subject_name: str, start: int, end: int) → Dict[int, float]¶

Calculate efficiency for one subject between the given trial range.

Parameters:

  • subject_name – The name of the subject.

  • start – The starting trial number (inclusive).

  • end – The ending trial number (exclusive).

Returns:

A dictionary with trial numbers as keys and efficiency values as values.

Return type:

Dict[int, float]

plot_for_these_subjects(subjects: List[str], start: int = 3, end: int = 23, save_only: bool = False)¶

Plot movement paths for a list of subjects between the given trial range.

Parameters:

  • subjects – A list of subject names.

  • start – The starting trial number (inclusive).

  • end – The ending trial number (exclusive).

  • save_only – If True, the plot will only be saved and not displayed.

plots_for_all_subjects(start=3, end=23, excluding=None, save_only=False)¶

Saves plots for all subjects in the dataset.

Args:

start (int): The index of the first trial to be plotted (inclusive). end (int): The index of the last trial to be plotted (exclusive). excluding (list): A list of subject names to be excluded from the plots. save_only (bool): If True, save the plots without showing them.

Returns:

None
